= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =
configset  GLOBAL  addr_allow_comments_after_route = [VALEUR]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Valeur par défaut : no
Type de donnée    : booléen, entre : 0 n no, 1 y yes
Catégorie         : address
Mot de passe      : Visible avec un mot de passe.
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXEMPLE :
configset GLOBAL addr_allow_comments_after_route = 1


$INCLUDE-config/addr_allow_comments_after_route

Ceci est toujours légal :
   Joe Blow <joe@example.com>

Cela est uniquement accepté si "addr_allow_comments_after_route" est
actif :
   <joe@example.com> Joe Blow


Référez vous aussi à :
   help admin_domain
   help admin_subscribers
   help configset_addr_allow_at_in_phrase
   help configset_addr_allow_bang_paths
   help configset_addr_allow_ending_dot
   help configset_addr_limit_length
   help configset_addr_require_fqdn
   help configset_addr_strict_domain_check

$INCLUDE-help/foot
